[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772607622084,"sessionID":"ses_3485e2e92ffeioa887yBGG3ht2","part":{"id":"prt_cb7a5b6070019FZNfK4jaGDYGG","sessionID":"ses_3485e2e92ffeioa887yBGG3ht2","messageID":"msg_cb7a5a8ae001t8IEeadqdcD9B3","type":"text","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout design in tscircuit with USB-C and LED, disabled autorouting via `routingDisabled`, and avoided tscircuit registry components.\n\n- Updated `index.circuit.tsx` to define a compact breakout board (`36mm x 24mm`) with `routingDisabled` on `<board />`.\n- Imported JLCPCB parts directly with `tsci import --jlcpcb`:\n  - `imports/RP2040.tsx` (`C2040`)\n  - `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx` (`C165948`)\n- Added basic support circuitry in `index.circuit.tsx`:\n  - USB-C CC pull-downs (`R2`, `R3`, 5.1k)\n  - RP2040 core decoupling caps (`C1`, `C2`)\n  - Status LED path on `GPIO25` (`R1` + `D1`)\n- Wired connectivity using `connections={{ ... }}` nets while keeping routing disabled, so no autorouter dependency is used.\n- Used JLCPCB supplier part numbers for passive/LED placements in `index.circuit.tsx` to keep sourcing aligned.\n\nBuild executed as requested:\n\n- Ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript`\n- Output generated successfully in `dist/` (including `dist/index/circuit.json`)\n\nAssumptions used:\n- Minimal breakout scope is RP2040 + USB-C + LED + essential passive support, without full flash/clock/debug header population.","time":{"start":1772607622082,"end":1772607622082}}}

